@SlugFiller it's good to know that even despite its problems Tox is better than many other programs :). GNU has a lot of useful programs (they made an operating system...): https://www.gnu.org/software. This issue is about toxcore library, not the clients. As I said their requirements don't have anything to do with what features a program should have or how it should look like. You can disagree with some of the requirements, but just because some GNU program has issues, doesn't mean joining their project would be bad for us. Tox has a lot of problems too.

I don't know if it's possible to join KDE. Since they are a desktop environment, they probably only care about graphical programs? Toxcore has no UI.

We don't have to join any organisation, if we can just create our own and collect donations by ourselves. I'm only asking to do something as soon as possible.
